@drax68 another thing you could experiment with here is 

3) turn on row caching for the span_names table. you can do this quickly in cqlsh with

```
ALTER TABLE zipkin.span_names WITH caching = {'keys': 'ALL', 'rows_per_partition': "ALL"};
```

(still not getting github notifications, quite frustrating)

@yurishkuro (i do believe) you can avoid this problem by `startTs = max(startTs,  TimeUnit.MILLISECONDS.toMicros(System.currentTimeMillis()) - TimeUnit.SECONDS.toMicros(ttl));` in Repository.getTraceIdsByDuration(..)

That is you can avoid queries going into those buckets that we already know are only going to be filled with tombstones.
